# AGENTS.override.md (Personal Local Override)

<!--
HOW TO USE THIS FILE
====================

1. Copy this file to AGENTS.override.md (drop the .example suffix)
2. Edit it with your personal local preferences
3. It is gitignored by default — your overrides stay on your machine
4. Codex reads it natively at any directory level
5. Claude Code does not read it natively; if you want Claude Code to
   pick it up, add `@AGENTS.override.md` to your local CLAUDE.md
   (but NOT to the committed CLAUDE.md, since that would defeat the point)

WHEN TO USE OVERRIDES
=====================

- You prefer a different code style than the team's default (in your own working copy)
- You're temporarily debugging and want different test commands
- You want to disable certain rules during a refactor
- You're using a different shell, OS, or toolchain than the team default

DO NOT use this file for project-wide rules. Those go in AGENTS.md.
-->

## Personal Preferences

- I use [your shell, e.g., fish] instead of bash. Translate shell snippets accordingly.
- When committing, I prefer [your style, e.g., conventional commits with emoji prefixes].
- I'm currently focused on [the area you're working in this week]. Bias toward changes there.

## Temporary Debugging

<!-- Uncomment and modify when debugging -->
<!--
- The CI is broken for issue #[number]. Skip the [test command] step until merged.
- I'm running a local fork of [dependency] from [path]. Don't try to update it.
-->

## Tooling

- My local DB runs on port [port] (different from team default).
- I have [tool] installed at [non-standard path]. Use that path explicitly.

